## Error Handling

### HTTP Status Codes

| Code | Meaning | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| 200 | OK | Request successful |
| 400 | Bad Request | Invalid parameters |
| 401 | Unauthorized | Missing or invalid API key |
| 403 | Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |
| 404 | Not Found | Endpoint or resource doesn't exist |
| 429 | Too Many Requests | Rate limit exceeded |
| 500 | Internal Server Error | Server-side error |
| 503 | Service Unavailable | Temporary maintenance |

### Error Codes

| Code | Description | Solution |
|------|-------------|----------|
| `INVALID_ASSET` | Asset not supported | Check supported assets list |
| `INVALID_TIMEFRAME` | Timeframe parameter invalid | Use: 1m, 5m, 1h, 4h, 1d |
| `RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED` | Too many requests | Wait or upgrade tier |
| `INSUFFICIENT_DATA` | Not enough data for analysis | Try different timeframe |
| `API_KEY_EXPIRED` | API key no longer valid | Renew your subscription |
| `INSUFFICIENT_PERMISSIONS` | Feature requires higher tier | Upgrade account |

